Text:
Hey STF, great work as always...

Once the Wednesday release rush finishes, I was hoping you might take another couple of requests.  I'm trying to fill in some holes in my collection of completed runs:

I noticed you had Aspen's Soulfire Vol 1 trade in your latest batch (thanks for all of those, too!), but was wondering if you had a full set of Soulfire v3, which I can't locate.

Also, Mr Downtown had a torrent of Oni Press' Resurrection v2, but it isn't being seeded, and he hasn't been around in about a month, so if you happen to have the full Resurrection v2, a new up and/or seeding the existing torrent would be mighty handy. 

And, if asking one more isn't too much, There doesn't seem to be a torrent of Stitched 8, 9, or 10 anywhere. Thanks again!

sounds good to me. the thing about soulfire, i had downloaded that, and i went to comixology because it was confusing me -- i think it was the only release they've done for any volumes of that series. (so it may be hard to find v3, but i'll try.)

stitched is the same story, i downloaded 11 and 12 the other day, but like you've noticed, there are a few missing in the middle.

but yeah sure, i'll look tomorrow or the next day, time permitting.
Hey STFmaryville, is there any chance you have Outsiders V3?
i downloaded this to 2 laptops and they both have error.anyone else have trouble with this one?
what's the error? it works fine for me, but then again, TPB uploading has been wacky today...

dannyxt0, you can grab Outsiders v3 from this torrent:

http://thepiratebay.sx/torrent/6673132/

This is really Awesome! Thank you very much!

But Could I make a request please. Could you please upload Red hood and The Outlaws #18 I cant find it anywhere. Thank you very much!
ZombieHero, it's right here. the uploader simply forgot the issue number.
Oh, thank you very very much. I didnt trust it at first because I had no idea which it would be.

no problem. if you look at the "Files:   " line item at the top of a torrent page here on TPB, you can click the number ("1", in this case). i did that and saw the issue # in the actual file name. hope this helps!
